    <title id="55">Editing Interface Settings</title>
    <shortdesc id="56">You can change the settings for a host interface.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author id="57">Jim Owens</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N1001E_N1001B_N10001" id="58">
            <p id="59">The ability to change the interface settings is especially useful for
                updating the management interface. When a compute node is first created, its
                management interface is automatically set up using the default
                    <nameliteral id="70">Interface Type</nameliteral> (<nameliteral id="71">ethernet</nameliteral>).
                If you are using LAG on the management network, you must update this manually to
                    <nameliteral id="72">aggregated ethernet</nameliteral>.</p>
            <p id="82">You can also edit a management or infrastructure interface to attach
                to a data network by selecting <uicontrol id="83">data</uicontrol> as an
                additional Network Type for the interface, or using the CLI. For CLI instructions,
                see <xref href="jow1427029415968.xml" id="86"/>.</p>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/lock_host" id="step_N1003F_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" id="73">
                <cmd id="74"/>
            </step>
            <step conref="jow1426453628262.xml#jow1426453628262/open_details_locked_host" id="step_N10048_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" id="75">
                <cmd id="76"/>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10069_N10028_N1001C_N10001" id="20">
                <cmd id="21">Select the<uicontrol id="22"> Interfaces</uicontrol>
                    tab to display the existing interfaces.</cmd>
                <info id="84">
                    <fig id="fig_N1007E_N1007B_N10068_N10028_N1001C_N10001" id="26">
                        <image alt="Interfaces list" href="jow1404333527705.image" id="image_i45_25z_jn" id="54" width="5.5in"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N1009A_N10027_N1001B_N10001" id="60">
                <cmd id="61">Click <uicontrol id="62">Edit Interface</uicontrol> for the interface you want to
                    change.</cmd>
                <info id="63">
                    <fig id="fig_xfz_5fm_vp" id="64">
                        <image href="jow1426954976474.image" id="image_w5l_tlk_lr" id="24" width="4in">
                            <alt id="85">TiS Edit Interface</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                    <!-- p>If you are changing the <nameliteral>Interface Type</nameliteral> to
                            <nameliteral>aggregated ethernet</nameliteral>, select the second port
                        connected to the network.</p -->
                    <!-- JO 2015-03-24 screenshot? sounds plausible, but I don't see a second port -->
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100BB_N10027_N1001B_N10001" id="67">
                <cmd id="68">Make the required changes, and then click <uicontrol id="69">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                <info id="79">
                    <p id="80">For information about the available settings, see <xref href="jow1426955886080.xml" id="81"/>.</p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N100B2_N1003C_N1001F_N10001" id="77">
                <cmd id="78">Unlock the host.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task-wr>